1
00:01:26,580 --> 00:01:34,950
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,340 --> 00:01:37,940
[Episode 10]

3
00:01:52,110 --> 00:01:55,350
[Snack Shop]

4
00:02:01,070 --> 00:02:04,450
[Snack Shop]

5
00:02:01,650 --> 00:02:02,310
Xu Shengli.

6
00:02:18,210 --> 00:02:20,690
His parents and my mom are old friends.

7
00:02:22,030 --> 00:02:22,930
I was able to come to Beijing

8
00:02:22,930 --> 00:02:24,460
and take classes with Mr. Zheng

9
00:02:24,460 --> 00:02:26,390
thanks to Kang Shunyin's parents.

10
00:02:28,300 --> 00:02:29,900
We're very grateful to them.

11
00:02:30,930 --> 00:02:32,730
Not long after classes started,

12
00:02:33,090 --> 00:02:34,150
Kang Shunyin's mother

13
00:02:34,150 --> 00:02:35,470
suddenly said she wanted to set

14
00:02:35,470 --> 00:02:36,800
Kang Shunyin up with me.

15
00:02:37,410 --> 00:02:38,610
We met a few times.

16
00:02:39,060 --> 00:02:40,610
But I realized that he was

17
00:02:40,860 --> 00:02:42,460
very emotionally unstable.

18
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:43,630
And in his daily life,

19
00:02:43,630 --> 00:02:45,490
he seemed like a total mama's boy.

20
00:02:46,130 --> 00:02:48,130
We were definitely not a good match.

21
00:02:50,710 --> 00:02:51,579
So my mom and I

22
00:02:51,590 --> 00:02:53,650
set things straight with his family.

23
00:02:54,930 --> 00:02:56,450
But after a while,

24
00:02:56,930 --> 00:02:58,370
rumors started spreading in town

25
00:02:58,370 --> 00:03:00,900
that Kang Shunyin and I
were getting engaged.

26
00:03:01,370 --> 00:03:02,810
His family spread them.

27
00:03:04,590 --> 00:03:06,180
Before we could even argue with them,

28
00:03:06,180 --> 00:03:08,500
they sent gold and silver jewelry,

29
00:03:08,970 --> 00:03:09,930
and all sorts of stuff

30
00:03:09,930 --> 00:03:10,940
to my house.

31
00:03:11,150 --> 00:03:12,610
We refused them on the spot

32
00:03:12,740 --> 00:03:14,240
and returned everything.

33
00:03:15,470 --> 00:03:17,400
But they wouldn't listen to a word.

34
00:03:18,780 --> 00:03:20,470
Then they started making trouble
for no reason.

35
00:03:20,470 --> 00:03:22,250
That's just shameless!

36
00:03:22,750 --> 00:03:23,970
You made it clear

37
00:03:23,970 --> 00:03:24,970
and rejected him.

38
00:03:25,590 --> 00:03:27,910
How dare he still
come to Beijing to find you?

39
00:03:27,910 --> 00:03:28,670
He's sick.

40
00:03:34,180 --> 00:03:35,420
Actually, I'm okay.

41
00:03:36,430 --> 00:03:37,690
It's mainly my family.

42
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:40,450
They're in a tough spot.

43
00:03:42,190 --> 00:03:43,850
I feel really guilty about it.

44
00:03:45,470 --> 00:03:46,290
True.

45
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:48,530
In small towns like that,

46
00:03:48,530 --> 00:03:50,390
everyone knows everyone.

47
00:03:50,970 --> 00:03:53,700
Families have known each other
for generations.

48
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:55,500
You bump into them everywhere.

49
00:03:55,500 --> 00:03:57,950
It must be awkward for your parents.

50
00:04:08,300 --> 00:04:09,230
Have you been...

51
00:04:10,150 --> 00:04:11,350
following me lately?

52
00:04:12,590 --> 00:04:14,650
I... I was just worried

53
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:16,120
he might come find you again

54
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:17,480
and do something crazy.

55
00:04:20,269 --> 00:04:20,890
Thank you.

56
00:04:22,870 --> 00:04:25,070
And thanks for changing the lock for us.

57
00:04:26,420 --> 00:04:27,990
No problem. No big deal.

58
00:04:28,420 --> 00:04:29,080
No big deal.

59
00:04:31,210 --> 00:04:31,890
Isn't the film crew

60
00:04:31,890 --> 00:04:33,030
pretty busy lately?

61
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:34,630
You don't need to worry.

62
00:04:34,630 --> 00:04:35,690
If anything really happens,

63
00:04:35,690 --> 00:04:36,890
I'll call the police.

64
00:04:38,250 --> 00:04:39,460
Wait a second.

65
00:04:55,100 --> 00:04:56,450
This is pepper spray.

66
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:58,170
It's really strong.

67
00:04:58,270 --> 00:04:59,050
I tried it.

68
00:04:59,390 --> 00:05:00,920
It sprays really far. Look.

69
00:05:01,620 --> 00:05:02,180
This far.

70
00:05:02,750 --> 00:05:03,120
Here.

71
00:05:03,540 --> 00:05:04,680
If you meet a bad guy in the future,

72
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:05,300
aim at him,

73
00:05:05,310 --> 00:05:06,250
and just... just spray.

74
00:05:06,250 --> 00:05:06,910
Just spray.

75
00:05:06,930 --> 00:05:08,370
He definitely won't be able to handle it.

76
00:05:08,370 --> 00:05:09,000
Try it.

77
00:05:14,370 --> 00:05:16,070
I... I'm not a bad guy.

78
00:05:22,690 --> 00:05:23,390
Now that I have

79
00:05:23,390 --> 00:05:24,720
such a powerful weapon,

80
00:05:25,130 --> 00:05:26,790
I won't be afraid of anything.

81
00:05:35,330 --> 00:05:36,890
Are you going to the set today?

82
00:05:36,890 --> 00:05:37,300
Yes.

83
00:05:37,860 --> 00:05:38,620
Ranran said she's also going to

84
00:05:38,620 --> 00:05:39,740
audition for your film crew.

85
00:05:39,740 --> 00:05:41,200
Audition for my film crew?

86
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:42,700
Zongbao introduced her.

87
00:05:42,980 --> 00:05:43,640
Zongbao...

88
00:05:47,420 --> 00:05:48,940
That Guo Zongbao, he...

89
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:52,620
He's abusing his power!

90
00:05:52,620 --> 00:05:54,300
Father, let me explain.

91
00:05:54,450 --> 00:05:55,600
It's not like that.

92
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:56,650
Ruping,

93
00:05:56,950 --> 00:05:58,650
you'll be the death of me!

94
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:02,390
I brought you back to this manor,

95
00:06:02,570 --> 00:06:03,730
but I never expected

96
00:06:04,180 --> 00:06:05,620
that you would turn my home

97
00:06:05,620 --> 00:06:08,130
upside down!

98
00:06:15,190 --> 00:06:15,750
Father,

99
00:06:16,510 --> 00:06:18,730
I have a humble status in this family.

100
00:06:19,130 --> 00:06:21,070
How would I dare to be unruly?

101
00:06:22,180 --> 00:06:22,660
Cut.

102
00:06:25,690 --> 00:06:26,920
Not bad.

103
00:06:27,620 --> 00:06:28,820
I noticed something.

104
00:06:28,890 --> 00:06:29,810
Just now,

105
00:06:29,860 --> 00:06:31,010
your expression

106
00:06:31,010 --> 00:06:32,010
when you knelt down

107
00:06:32,010 --> 00:06:33,870
and the expression when you looked up

108
00:06:33,870 --> 00:06:34,800
were different.

109
00:06:35,390 --> 00:06:36,970
Is this your own design?

110
00:06:37,330 --> 00:06:37,930
Director,

111
00:06:38,100 --> 00:06:39,840
when I was reading this scene,

112
00:06:39,950 --> 00:06:41,570
I could feel that this character

113
00:06:41,570 --> 00:06:43,030
might not be as direct

114
00:06:43,060 --> 00:06:44,100
or as silly

115
00:06:44,159 --> 00:06:44,820
as she acts.

116
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,750
Although it's just
a section of the script,

117
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:48,080
I can feel that

118
00:06:48,190 --> 00:06:49,740
this is a way to protect herself

119
00:06:49,740 --> 00:06:50,560
as an illegitimate daughter

120
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:52,010
in the household.

121
00:06:52,770 --> 00:06:53,750
Maybe because I'm also all alone

122
00:06:53,750 --> 00:06:54,680
out here,

123
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:55,720
I can really relate to

124
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:56,680
how she feels.

125
00:06:57,300 --> 00:06:57,790
Good.

126
00:06:57,890 --> 00:06:58,490
Of course,

127
00:06:58,810 --> 00:07:00,000
this scene is written

128
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,300
with such depth.

129
00:07:01,420 --> 00:07:02,810
I can totally feel

130
00:07:02,860 --> 00:07:04,630
the screenwriter's dedication.

131
00:07:04,630 --> 00:07:06,570
The screenwriter
not only understood the character,

132
00:07:06,570 --> 00:07:08,030
but also made such a small role

133
00:07:08,030 --> 00:07:09,310
so well-rounded.

134
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:10,920
It's really amazing.

135
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:12,100
Amazing.

136
00:07:15,300 --> 00:07:16,770
The Master was played well too.

137
00:07:16,770 --> 00:07:17,970
Thank you, Director.

138
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:19,160
It's just that

139
00:07:19,450 --> 00:07:20,550
the accent

140
00:07:21,630 --> 00:07:23,570
might not be suitable for the Master.

141
00:07:23,570 --> 00:07:24,250
So why not let him

142
00:07:24,250 --> 00:07:25,270
play the butler?

143
00:07:25,330 --> 00:07:26,180
Sure!

144
00:07:26,190 --> 00:07:27,460
Director, sure.

145
00:07:27,570 --> 00:07:28,430
A butler works too.

146
00:07:28,430 --> 00:07:29,390
Good.

147
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:29,950
I...

148
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,400
Go back and wait for news.

149
00:07:31,430 --> 00:07:32,680
-Thank you, sirs.
-Thank you, Director.

150
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:33,190
Thank you, everyone.

151
00:07:33,190 --> 00:07:33,480
Thank you.

152
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:34,430
Next group, get ready.

153
00:07:34,430 --> 00:07:35,390
Okay.

154
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:38,360
This scene is written quite well.

155
00:07:39,010 --> 00:07:39,470
Indeed.

156
00:07:40,110 --> 00:07:41,230
Whose idea was it?

157
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:42,760
It was all Xu's idea.

158
00:07:45,190 --> 00:07:45,520
Good.

159
00:07:46,310 --> 00:07:46,690
Good.

160
00:07:48,830 --> 00:07:49,500
Next group.

161
00:07:49,690 --> 00:07:50,750
Are you ready?

162
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:52,040
Ready, Director.

163
00:07:55,010 --> 00:07:56,340
Great Screenwriter Xu,

164
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:57,830
have some pig trotters.

165
00:07:58,390 --> 00:08:00,080
We've all studied

166
00:08:00,250 --> 00:08:02,260
the script you wrote.

167
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:04,770
It's written so well.

168
00:08:05,330 --> 00:08:07,580
If I could really act in it,

169
00:08:07,870 --> 00:08:09,770
could you give me some pointers?

170
00:08:09,860 --> 00:08:11,320
I can't give you pointers.

171
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:14,000
You're treating me like a stranger, too.

172
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:14,720
You think I won't help you

173
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:15,580
if you just ask?

174
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:17,480
What is this?

175
00:08:17,770 --> 00:08:18,530
The crew

176
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:20,200
has rules.

177
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,080
I can't get you in trouble.

178
00:08:22,360 --> 00:08:23,680
If I really asked you for it,

179
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:24,940
would you give it to me?

180
00:08:25,100 --> 00:08:25,500
Right?

181
00:08:26,780 --> 00:08:28,640
Have some trotters. Don't be shy.

182
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:31,050
Eat it yourself.

183
00:08:31,270 --> 00:08:32,309
It's hot.

184
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:36,909
Shen!

185
00:08:39,549 --> 00:08:40,150
Mr. Xu.

186
00:08:43,700 --> 00:08:45,030
I also want to thank you.

187
00:08:47,950 --> 00:08:49,360
Thanking me empty-handed?

188
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:49,690
Here.

189
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:51,710
It's hot!

190
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:55,960
Big pig trotters stewed by Mr. Guo.

191
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:57,100
I contributed.

192
00:08:57,340 --> 00:08:58,820
A little token of appreciation
from both of us

193
00:08:58,820 --> 00:09:00,740
for the future great screenwriter.

194
00:09:00,740 --> 00:09:01,580
Great screenwriter.

195
00:09:01,580 --> 00:09:02,550
What are we eating today?

196
00:09:02,550 --> 00:09:04,050
Why does it smell so good?

197
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:06,510
Pig trotters!

198
00:09:07,670 --> 00:09:08,030
What?

199
00:09:08,030 --> 00:09:09,580
It's for the great screenwriter.

200
00:09:09,580 --> 00:09:10,360
Exactly.

201
00:09:12,030 --> 00:09:12,580
Hey...

202
00:09:13,130 --> 00:09:14,590
You're dressed so nicely.

203
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,100
Where are you going?

204
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:17,830
Who are you going on a date with?

205
00:09:18,620 --> 00:09:20,300
Zhuang Zhuang styled me.

206
00:09:20,790 --> 00:09:21,790
Does it look good?

207
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:23,000
It looks good.

208
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:26,440
If I audition for
the song and dance troupe,

209
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,240
I could ask her

210
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:28,270
to help style me too.

211
00:09:28,270 --> 00:09:29,700
You want to audition
for the song and dance troupe?

212
00:09:29,700 --> 00:09:31,190
Come on.

213
00:09:31,700 --> 00:09:32,770
Have some trotters.

214
00:09:32,770 --> 00:09:34,100
One per person. Come on.

215
00:09:34,770 --> 00:09:35,750
Our lives

216
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:37,080
are getting better and better.

217
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:38,050
-It’s for the scriptwriter.
-From now on,

218
00:09:38,050 --> 00:09:39,860
we'll eat trotters every day, okay?

219
00:09:39,860 --> 00:09:40,190
Here.

220
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:41,900
Have some more.

221
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:44,740
Here's the audition plan I just wrote.

222
00:09:44,740 --> 00:09:45,210
Take a look.

223
00:09:45,210 --> 00:09:45,600
Okay.

224
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:46,590
Let me see.

225
00:09:46,890 --> 00:09:48,430
-Is it good?
-It’s so delicious.

226
00:09:48,430 --> 00:09:50,460
Look how excited Xuan is.

227
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:51,680
Decline.

228
00:09:52,100 --> 00:09:53,930
Poetry is eternal.

229
00:09:54,270 --> 00:09:55,870
Now, all over the streets...

230
00:09:56,870 --> 00:09:59,000
It can make the living die,

231
00:09:59,740 --> 00:10:01,460
and the dead come back to life.

232
00:10:02,050 --> 00:10:02,790
This hatred,

233
00:10:03,170 --> 00:10:04,320
formless,

234
00:10:04,820 --> 00:10:06,120
is held in the palm

235
00:10:06,580 --> 00:10:07,650
like a thorn.

236
00:10:09,030 --> 00:10:10,790
When I no longer cling to love,

237
00:10:11,390 --> 00:10:13,450
when I'm no longer trapped in hate...

238
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:07,200
All right.

239
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:08,440
That's enough, candidate.

240
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:09,160
Sir,

241
00:11:09,820 --> 00:11:11,750
I haven't played the best part yet.

242
00:11:12,630 --> 00:11:13,200
That will do.

243
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,330
We've heard enough.

244
00:11:15,510 --> 00:11:16,910
Next candidate, please.

245
00:11:17,750 --> 00:11:18,700
Thank you, sirs.

246
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:22,010
See? You made the list.

247
00:11:22,010 --> 00:11:23,140
Right in the middle.

248
00:11:23,370 --> 00:11:24,630
That's me. Did you see?

249
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:26,460
How about that?

250
00:11:27,760 --> 00:11:28,380
[Fenghua Song and Dance Troupe Results]
[Musicians]

251
00:11:28,410 --> 00:11:30,060
[Backup Singers]

252
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:31,240
[Backup Dancers]

253
00:11:41,390 --> 00:11:43,050
I told you I'd get in this time.

254
00:11:43,050 --> 00:11:43,910
What do you say?

255
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:45,300
You're confident.

256
00:11:45,790 --> 00:11:46,320
Let's go.

257
00:11:55,270 --> 00:11:55,870
Hello, Director.

258
00:11:55,870 --> 00:11:57,220
My name is Tao Liangliang.

259
00:11:57,220 --> 00:11:58,080
I just

260
00:11:58,390 --> 00:11:59,150
checked the list.

261
00:11:59,150 --> 00:12:00,210
My name isn't on it.

262
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:01,440
I wanted to ask

263
00:12:02,340 --> 00:12:03,470
wh-what's going on?

264
00:12:06,090 --> 00:12:07,010
Come on in.

265
00:12:08,860 --> 00:12:09,460
Thank you.

266
00:12:11,700 --> 00:12:12,630
Well...

267
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:14,100
Here's the thing.

268
00:12:14,220 --> 00:12:15,510
Since the list is already posted,

269
00:12:15,510 --> 00:12:16,640
and you're not on it,

270
00:12:16,910 --> 00:12:18,910
you can try again next year.

271
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:21,400
But I've auditioned twice already.

272
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:22,360
I've even come here

273
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:23,560
several times.

274
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:25,660
-Twice isn't a lot.
-I just want…

275
00:12:25,940 --> 00:12:26,890
Some people

276
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:29,560
try seven or eight times
and still don't get in.

277
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:32,290
Director, since I'm here today,

278
00:12:32,290 --> 00:12:34,090
can I play a piece just for you...

279
00:12:35,790 --> 00:12:37,330
in your office?

280
00:12:37,370 --> 00:12:37,910
Now, now.

281
00:12:37,940 --> 00:12:38,870
No need, no need.

282
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:40,330
Take it easy.

283
00:12:40,530 --> 00:12:41,260
Take it easy.

284
00:12:42,750 --> 00:12:43,320
Here.

285
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:44,460
Come, sit down.

286
00:12:47,440 --> 00:12:48,300
Young man,

287
00:12:48,750 --> 00:12:50,410
you've already auditioned for our troupe,

288
00:12:50,410 --> 00:12:51,050
so we've definitely heard

289
00:12:51,050 --> 00:12:52,110
your performance.

290
00:12:54,050 --> 00:12:55,310
Here's the situation.

291
00:12:55,410 --> 00:12:56,610
This year, our troupe

292
00:12:56,940 --> 00:12:58,150
has a very limited quota

293
00:12:58,150 --> 00:12:59,390
for saxophone players.

294
00:12:59,390 --> 00:13:00,510
We need

295
00:13:00,510 --> 00:13:02,220
extremely professional people.

296
00:13:02,220 --> 00:13:04,000
I'm very professional.

297
00:13:04,390 --> 00:13:05,270
Director, look.

298
00:13:05,270 --> 00:13:06,460
I've been dreaming day and night

299
00:13:06,460 --> 00:13:07,410
about joining this troupe.

300
00:13:07,410 --> 00:13:09,010
If I can get in,

301
00:13:09,170 --> 00:13:10,550
I'll put my heart and soul

302
00:13:10,550 --> 00:13:12,120
into performing for everyone.

303
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:13,010
If you tell me to climb a mountain,

304
00:13:13,010 --> 00:13:14,580
I won't just lie in the grass.

305
00:13:14,580 --> 00:13:15,550
Whatever you tell me to do,

306
00:13:15,550 --> 00:13:16,480
I'll do it.

307
00:13:16,670 --> 00:13:17,410
And I'm not afraid

308
00:13:17,410 --> 00:13:19,010
of hardship or fatigue.

309
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:20,240
-I…
-Okay, okay.

310
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:21,190
This kid...

311
00:13:22,910 --> 00:13:23,770
How about this?

312
00:13:24,770 --> 00:13:25,630
Let me ask you,

313
00:13:26,100 --> 00:13:27,480
who is

314
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:28,480
your sax teacher?

315
00:13:32,130 --> 00:13:34,390
I had a teacher when I was young,

316
00:13:34,910 --> 00:13:36,050
but later I...

317
00:13:36,070 --> 00:13:36,870
Self-taught?

318
00:13:37,440 --> 00:13:37,860
Yes.

319
00:13:39,390 --> 00:13:40,390
Here's the thing.

320
00:13:40,860 --> 00:13:42,710
I have a suggestion for you.

321
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:44,400
Find a teacher

322
00:13:45,270 --> 00:13:46,130
and seriously,

323
00:13:46,290 --> 00:13:48,890
systematically,
start with the basics again.

324
00:13:54,860 --> 00:13:56,920
Lamb skewers! Get your lamb skewers!

325
00:14:12,100 --> 00:14:13,430
What are you doing here?

326
00:14:13,620 --> 00:14:15,820
You knew it was me without even looking?

327
00:14:20,670 --> 00:14:21,080
Sit.

328
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:29,670
Every day when I wake up,

329
00:14:31,770 --> 00:14:33,960
I look at that tiny half-window.

330
00:14:34,620 --> 00:14:36,280
With people coming and going,

331
00:14:37,050 --> 00:14:38,490
all I can see

332
00:14:39,770 --> 00:14:41,240
are their shoes.

333
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:49,250
I live like a mole every day.

334
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:52,250
I was able to hold on

335
00:14:54,630 --> 00:14:56,830
only because of that little bit of hope.

336
00:15:06,120 --> 00:15:07,310
I heard about it.

337
00:15:08,340 --> 00:15:09,440
I saw you weren't in your room

338
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:11,570
and I couldn't find you anywhere else,

339
00:15:12,780 --> 00:15:14,040
so I came here to check.

340
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:19,130
Why were you looking for me?

341
00:15:19,770 --> 00:15:21,320
To... To laugh at you.

342
00:15:21,340 --> 00:15:22,230
Laugh at me?

343
00:15:26,170 --> 00:15:27,560
I've got thick skin.

344
00:15:32,670 --> 00:15:33,460
Liangliang,

345
00:15:35,530 --> 00:15:36,990
you seriously play the sax

346
00:15:37,040 --> 00:15:38,950
really well.

347
00:15:39,130 --> 00:15:41,190
It's not that you're not good enough.

348
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:43,040
It's that they have no taste.

349
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:44,190
Really.

350
00:15:44,510 --> 00:15:47,040
They just don't know quality
when they see it.

351
00:15:55,530 --> 00:15:56,870
As long as you do.

352
00:16:00,630 --> 00:16:01,690
Let's have a drink.

353
00:16:03,930 --> 00:16:05,430
There's a new bottle here.

354
00:16:09,240 --> 00:16:09,700
Here.

355
00:16:16,850 --> 00:16:18,820
Dad, Dad. Here.
Give it to me. Let me do it.

356
00:16:18,820 --> 00:16:19,870
Let me do it for you.

357
00:16:19,870 --> 00:16:20,480
No, no, no.

358
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:23,320
No need.
Those hands are for playing the saxophone.

359
00:16:23,320 --> 00:16:24,620
I rarely get to come back.

360
00:16:24,620 --> 00:16:25,270
Let me help you.

361
00:16:25,270 --> 00:16:26,530
Look at this. How is it?

362
00:16:27,620 --> 00:16:29,110
My skills have improved, right?

363
00:16:29,110 --> 00:16:30,670
Look at how I flip these.

364
00:16:30,700 --> 00:16:32,270
Here, Mom, Dad.

365
00:16:32,370 --> 00:16:34,170
Let me pour for both of you.

366
00:16:40,700 --> 00:16:41,310
Okay.

367
00:16:43,150 --> 00:16:44,070
Why do I have

368
00:16:44,100 --> 00:16:45,500
a bad feeling about this?

369
00:16:47,030 --> 00:16:48,970
Dad, you're too paranoid.

370
00:16:49,030 --> 00:16:51,090
I've learned my lessons the hard way.

371
00:16:51,270 --> 00:16:52,800
Raising you all these years

372
00:16:52,940 --> 00:16:55,070
has taught me more than the real world.

373
00:16:56,500 --> 00:16:57,040
Dad,

374
00:16:57,370 --> 00:16:59,300
well, you're the one who taught me.

375
00:16:59,390 --> 00:17:00,820
I taught you how to cook,

376
00:17:01,010 --> 00:17:02,980
but I didn't teach you
how to play that thing.

377
00:17:02,980 --> 00:17:04,839
You picked that up all on your own.

378
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:06,960
Alright. Hurry up and eat.

379
00:17:07,050 --> 00:17:08,380
Let's talk while we eat.

380
00:17:08,680 --> 00:17:09,300
Mom, Dad,

381
00:17:10,089 --> 00:17:11,280
for over 20 years,

382
00:17:11,880 --> 00:17:13,630
I've made you two worry a lot.

383
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:16,150
As a son,

384
00:17:17,790 --> 00:17:18,609
I'm not the same

385
00:17:18,609 --> 00:17:19,940
as other people's sons.

386
00:17:20,310 --> 00:17:21,710
I haven't made you proud.

387
00:17:22,010 --> 00:17:23,260
But I swear,

388
00:17:24,160 --> 00:17:25,000
in the future,

389
00:17:25,290 --> 00:17:26,640
if I make something of myself

390
00:17:26,640 --> 00:17:28,180
and make it big,

391
00:17:28,880 --> 00:17:29,770
I promise

392
00:17:30,070 --> 00:17:31,670
I'll treat you like royalty.

393
00:17:32,110 --> 00:17:32,770
Bottoms up!

394
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:34,770
You...

395
00:17:35,460 --> 00:17:36,960
Doing this all of a sudden,

396
00:17:36,960 --> 00:17:37,920
it's not just your dad who's confused.

397
00:17:37,920 --> 00:17:38,940
Even I feel

398
00:17:38,940 --> 00:17:40,470
a bit uneasy.

399
00:17:40,550 --> 00:17:42,290
See? What did I tell you?

400
00:17:44,330 --> 00:17:45,510
Recently,

401
00:17:46,590 --> 00:17:48,320
I've figured some things out.

402
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:51,400
I've been thinking it over,
and it doesn't feel right.

403
00:17:51,530 --> 00:17:52,380
So,

404
00:17:54,460 --> 00:17:55,310
I won't carry

405
00:17:56,420 --> 00:17:57,550
this sax around

406
00:17:57,550 --> 00:17:58,480
to busk anymore.

407
00:18:00,330 --> 00:18:01,570
I'll work hard

408
00:18:02,250 --> 00:18:03,580
and turn over a new leaf!

409
00:18:04,920 --> 00:18:06,390
Pinch me.

410
00:18:06,500 --> 00:18:08,120
I feel like I'm dreaming.

411
00:18:09,070 --> 00:18:09,880
He's grown up.

412
00:18:10,310 --> 00:18:11,370
He's sensible now.

413
00:18:11,480 --> 00:18:12,220
Have some food.

414
00:18:12,220 --> 00:18:13,800
Taste your son's cooking.

415
00:18:14,510 --> 00:18:16,080
Come on, try it.

416
00:18:19,850 --> 00:18:21,310
You're really something,

417
00:18:22,460 --> 00:18:23,110
Son,

418
00:18:23,160 --> 00:18:24,620
what do you plan to do next?

419
00:18:24,790 --> 00:18:26,310
Tell us as soon as you've decided.

420
00:18:26,310 --> 00:18:26,720
I...

421
00:18:26,770 --> 00:18:27,700
No need to say it.

422
00:18:27,980 --> 00:18:29,240
I've already guessed.

423
00:18:30,050 --> 00:18:30,830
As soon as he came in,

424
00:18:30,830 --> 00:18:32,050
he took over my ladle,

425
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:34,090
wanting to show me his skills.

426
00:18:34,090 --> 00:18:35,430
You've been mad at me all these years,

427
00:18:35,430 --> 00:18:36,830
renting a place outside.

428
00:18:37,010 --> 00:18:38,750
But lately, I keep seeing you.

429
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:39,900
Quite a few times now.

430
00:18:39,900 --> 00:18:40,530
You've been hanging around

431
00:18:40,530 --> 00:18:42,250
the entrance of our restaurant.

432
00:18:42,250 --> 00:18:44,290
You bolt the moment I see you.

433
00:18:44,440 --> 00:18:45,160
Why?

434
00:18:45,350 --> 00:18:46,420
Is that even a question?

435
00:18:46,420 --> 00:18:47,960
You used to be so harsh.

436
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:49,100
He's afraid of you.

437
00:18:49,250 --> 00:18:51,920
If you want to learn the trade,
just say so.

438
00:18:52,030 --> 00:18:53,430
Nothing to be shy about.

439
00:18:53,790 --> 00:18:55,790
A returned prodigal
is worth more than gold.

440
00:18:55,790 --> 00:18:56,330
Today,

441
00:18:56,700 --> 00:18:58,510
I'll pass down our family's

442
00:18:58,510 --> 00:18:59,420
secret fried sauce recipe

443
00:18:59,420 --> 00:19:00,110
to you.

444
00:19:03,770 --> 00:19:04,240
Dad.

445
00:19:05,460 --> 00:19:07,360
Sometimes, I think

446
00:19:07,550 --> 00:19:09,180
playing the sax

447
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:11,110
doesn't have much of a future.

448
00:19:11,110 --> 00:19:11,760
Yeah.

449
00:19:11,790 --> 00:19:13,920
That thing won't put food on the table.

450
00:19:14,180 --> 00:19:15,530
You should've gotten rid of it long ago.

451
00:19:15,530 --> 00:19:17,660
Sometimes it can put food on the table.

452
00:19:17,680 --> 00:19:19,480
Maybe it can feed me even better.

453
00:19:19,500 --> 00:19:20,640
Look at this fried sauce.

454
00:19:20,640 --> 00:19:21,420
It has a mix of fatty and lean meat.

455
00:19:21,420 --> 00:19:22,920
Put the fatty meat in first.

456
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:24,220
Render it into cracklings.

457
00:19:24,220 --> 00:19:25,310
Then add the lean meat.

458
00:19:25,310 --> 00:19:25,680
No,

459
00:19:25,680 --> 00:19:27,140
use less of this fat.

460
00:19:27,140 --> 00:19:27,720
It's...

461
00:19:27,980 --> 00:19:28,750
too much.

462
00:19:29,090 --> 00:19:30,850
Then add some lean meat.

463
00:19:33,700 --> 00:19:35,030
Dad, I'll be straight with you.

464
00:19:35,030 --> 00:19:37,830
I want to audition
for a song and dance troupe here.

465
00:19:38,350 --> 00:19:40,400
The teachers there

466
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:41,680
think your son

467
00:19:42,330 --> 00:19:44,660
is a rising star

468
00:19:44,660 --> 00:19:46,580
with a bright future.

469
00:19:52,440 --> 00:19:53,930
Their troupe

470
00:19:54,610 --> 00:19:56,750
needs a sax player.

471
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:58,710
I happen to play the sax.

472
00:19:59,550 --> 00:20:01,010
I have to help them

473
00:20:01,010 --> 00:20:02,200
return to their former glory.

474
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:02,850
I need to step it up,

475
00:20:02,850 --> 00:20:03,870
so I need to hire

476
00:20:03,900 --> 00:20:04,480
an instructor

477
00:20:04,480 --> 00:20:05,880
to give me some pointers.

478
00:20:09,940 --> 00:20:10,720
I'll be frank.

479
00:20:10,720 --> 00:20:11,850
I need to pay

480
00:20:11,850 --> 00:20:13,290
in order to hire a sax teacher.

481
00:20:13,290 --> 00:20:14,740
I want to get some money

482
00:20:14,830 --> 00:20:15,890
from you and my mom.

483
00:20:15,940 --> 00:20:16,940
I'll pay you back.

484
00:20:22,160 --> 00:20:22,720
Dad,

485
00:20:22,920 --> 00:20:24,030
don't worry.

486
00:20:24,460 --> 00:20:25,700
I definitely won't let this money

487
00:20:25,700 --> 00:20:27,110
go down the drain.

488
00:20:27,220 --> 00:20:28,530
"Return what you borrow,
and it's easy to borrow again."

489
00:20:28,530 --> 00:20:29,070
Deal?

490
00:20:29,160 --> 00:20:30,160
Think about it.

491
00:20:30,160 --> 00:20:31,940
Let me toss the wok for you. Come on.

492
00:20:31,940 --> 00:20:32,640
Move.

493
00:20:32,640 --> 00:20:33,760
You do it? Let me.

494
00:20:33,850 --> 00:20:34,310
This...

495
00:20:35,680 --> 00:20:36,030
I...

496
00:20:44,150 --> 00:20:45,750
What's wrong? What's wrong?

497
00:20:47,270 --> 00:20:48,370
What happened?

498
00:20:49,300 --> 00:20:49,740
Brag.

499
00:20:50,550 --> 00:20:51,540
Brag harder!

500
00:20:52,160 --> 00:20:52,460
Dad.

501
00:20:53,070 --> 00:20:54,250
I wasn't bragging.

502
00:20:54,270 --> 00:20:55,330
Go play in the shop.

503
00:20:56,140 --> 00:20:56,900
Hold that

504
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:58,090
solid silver chamber pot of yours

505
00:20:58,090 --> 00:20:59,090
and go play in my shop.

506
00:20:59,090 --> 00:21:00,290
How could I?

507
00:21:00,290 --> 00:21:01,510
Listen to what he's saying.

508
00:21:01,510 --> 00:21:02,570
You need tuition?

509
00:21:02,850 --> 00:21:03,850
Earn it yourself!

510
00:21:03,870 --> 00:21:04,880
I'm hiring you.

511
00:21:05,610 --> 00:21:07,090
What exactly is going on?

512
00:21:07,140 --> 00:21:08,890
My son is scheming against me!

513
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:09,980
No—

514
00:21:12,240 --> 00:21:12,840
Your foot.

515
00:21:13,570 --> 00:21:14,900
-What happened to your foot?
-Dad.

516
00:21:14,900 --> 00:21:16,300
You're really paying me?

517
00:21:17,220 --> 00:21:19,680
I'm really going to
the shop tomorrow, then.

518
00:21:34,440 --> 00:21:36,420
Does this work?

519
00:21:41,550 --> 00:21:43,440
This painting today...

520
00:21:44,110 --> 00:21:45,510
looks a bit interesting.

521
00:21:46,790 --> 00:21:48,030
What do you mean by "interesting"?

522
00:21:48,030 --> 00:21:49,240
Interesting in what way?

523
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:51,500
What does "a bit interesting" even mean?

524
00:21:52,460 --> 00:21:54,270
It means...

525
00:21:54,330 --> 00:21:55,690
in this hot weather,

526
00:21:55,810 --> 00:21:57,070
under the blazing sun,

527
00:21:57,960 --> 00:22:00,160
seeing the hard work you put in, it's...

528
00:22:00,180 --> 00:22:01,180
not bad.

529
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:01,930
Pretty good.

530
00:22:02,770 --> 00:22:03,850
From what you're saying,

531
00:22:03,850 --> 00:22:05,450
you think my painting is bad.

532
00:22:07,660 --> 00:22:08,770
Everyone is different.

533
00:22:08,770 --> 00:22:09,350
It's subjective.

534
00:22:09,350 --> 00:22:10,940
There's no good or bad.

535
00:22:11,140 --> 00:22:13,880
It's just about
whether you like it or not.

536
00:22:13,980 --> 00:22:14,940
You watch me every day.

537
00:22:14,940 --> 00:22:16,110
Will things change
because you're watching?

538
00:22:16,110 --> 00:22:17,480
What you're doing

539
00:22:17,550 --> 00:22:18,330
is even more annoying

540
00:22:18,330 --> 00:22:19,660
than those bossy old men

541
00:22:19,680 --> 00:22:21,540
watching people watching chess.

542
00:22:21,680 --> 00:22:23,140
Oh, you...

543
00:22:25,030 --> 00:22:26,230
Let me put it this way.

544
00:22:27,270 --> 00:22:30,000
Let's be open and honest,

545
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:31,060
and tell the truth.

546
00:22:34,570 --> 00:22:36,330
We are in the same field.

547
00:22:37,880 --> 00:22:39,740
I'm also a painter.

548
00:22:42,660 --> 00:22:43,790
Don't use your hobby

549
00:22:43,810 --> 00:22:45,110
to compete with my passion.

550
00:22:45,110 --> 00:22:45,900
The peonies you learned to paint

551
00:22:45,900 --> 00:22:48,160
at the senior university doesn't count.

552
00:22:48,460 --> 00:22:49,590
I want to

553
00:22:50,380 --> 00:22:51,640
collaborate with you.

554
00:23:14,070 --> 00:23:15,390
What are you doing?

555
00:23:16,010 --> 00:23:17,470
You're playing way too loud.

556
00:23:17,470 --> 00:23:19,130
How is anyone supposed to eat?

557
00:23:19,140 --> 00:23:19,940
Get your boss.

558
00:23:21,440 --> 00:23:22,170
He's inside.

559
00:23:26,890 --> 00:23:27,850
Who's the boss?

560
00:23:29,250 --> 00:23:29,750
What's wrong?

561
00:23:29,750 --> 00:23:31,410
Is the food not to your liking?

562
00:23:31,570 --> 00:23:32,960
It's not about the food.

563
00:23:33,660 --> 00:23:34,990
It's that kid you hired.

564
00:23:35,050 --> 00:23:36,130
Playing that...

565
00:23:36,440 --> 00:23:37,350
that big horn.

566
00:23:37,660 --> 00:23:38,980
It scared me!

567
00:23:39,030 --> 00:23:40,240
That's not a horn.

568
00:23:40,330 --> 00:23:41,430
It's a sax.

569
00:23:41,850 --> 00:23:42,920
We just wanted to provide

570
00:23:42,920 --> 00:23:44,700
some entertainment for everyone.

571
00:23:44,700 --> 00:23:46,400
I'm just having a bowl of noodles.

572
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:47,440
What entertainment do I need?

573
00:23:47,440 --> 00:23:47,840
You...

574
00:23:48,110 --> 00:23:49,480
If you were serving a royal banquet,

575
00:23:49,480 --> 00:23:50,320
maybe then.

576
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:52,000
No, actually,

577
00:23:52,630 --> 00:23:54,140
even if I were eating a royal banquet,

578
00:23:54,140 --> 00:23:55,610
I still wouldn't listen to that junk.

579
00:23:55,610 --> 00:23:57,010
Tell him to stop right now.

580
00:23:57,010 --> 00:23:57,540
Alright.

581
00:23:57,940 --> 00:24:00,140
This plate of fried pork is on the house.

582
00:24:01,220 --> 00:24:02,620
Well, thanks. Thank you.

583
00:24:05,510 --> 00:24:06,050
Boss,

584
00:24:06,640 --> 00:24:08,240
why do you even bother?

585
00:24:08,640 --> 00:24:09,270
That kid

586
00:24:10,140 --> 00:24:11,690
looks like a hooligan.

587
00:24:11,900 --> 00:24:13,200
He doesn't look like he comes from

588
00:24:13,200 --> 00:24:14,330
a decent family.

589
00:24:15,220 --> 00:24:15,880
Why on earth

590
00:24:16,070 --> 00:24:17,240
would you hire him?

591
00:24:18,420 --> 00:24:19,420
Stop right there.

592
00:24:23,590 --> 00:24:24,670
What's this for?

593
00:24:24,880 --> 00:24:26,550
This food isn't suitable for you.

594
00:24:26,550 --> 00:24:28,480
I won't charge you for the noodles.

595
00:24:50,500 --> 00:24:52,840
This is my workshop.

596
00:24:53,940 --> 00:24:55,010
These young people

597
00:24:55,090 --> 00:24:56,500
are just like you.

598
00:24:56,900 --> 00:24:58,920
They come from all over the country.

599
00:24:59,550 --> 00:25:01,700
They used to be like you,

600
00:25:01,850 --> 00:25:02,930
roaming about.

601
00:25:04,660 --> 00:25:07,010
They couldn't make a living anymore,

602
00:25:07,030 --> 00:25:08,320
unable to afford food.

603
00:25:08,960 --> 00:25:09,880
It's tough.

604
00:25:10,700 --> 00:25:12,970
They call themselves artists

605
00:25:13,330 --> 00:25:14,680
but wear ragged underwear.

606
00:25:14,680 --> 00:25:15,460
Talk about art

607
00:25:15,460 --> 00:25:16,620
and they yap on and on

608
00:25:16,660 --> 00:25:18,000
through the night without stopping.

609
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:19,540
Talk to them about life

610
00:25:20,440 --> 00:25:21,500
and they go silent.

611
00:25:23,610 --> 00:25:25,940
I felt sorry for them,

612
00:25:26,090 --> 00:25:28,300
so I gathered them here.

613
00:25:30,320 --> 00:25:31,720
Room and board included.

614
00:25:31,830 --> 00:25:32,560
How about it?

615
00:25:32,810 --> 00:25:34,220
Do you want to join

616
00:25:34,290 --> 00:25:35,490
our big family?

617
00:25:38,050 --> 00:25:38,640
Art

618
00:25:39,610 --> 00:25:40,640
is ruined by people

619
00:25:40,640 --> 00:25:41,320
like you.

620
00:25:42,810 --> 00:25:43,570
Young man.

621
00:25:44,240 --> 00:25:46,100
The sea of bitterness is endless.

622
00:25:46,140 --> 00:25:46,850
You can't talk art

623
00:25:46,850 --> 00:25:48,500
on an empty stomach.

624
00:25:48,550 --> 00:25:50,960
You can only talk art when you're full.

625
00:25:51,610 --> 00:25:53,270
Think about it.

626
00:25:54,660 --> 00:25:55,140
Old man.

627
00:25:56,520 --> 00:25:58,160
"Man does not live by bread alone."

628
00:25:58,160 --> 00:25:58,620
Well...

629
00:25:58,680 --> 00:25:59,960
But judging by your air,

630
00:25:59,960 --> 00:26:00,790
I bet you don't even know

631
00:26:00,790 --> 00:26:01,920
who Dostoyevsky is.

632
00:26:01,960 --> 00:26:02,940
What?

633
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:03,860
Let me tell you.

634
00:26:03,920 --> 00:26:04,740
If I, Cao Ye,

635
00:26:05,070 --> 00:26:06,000
one day

636
00:26:06,010 --> 00:26:07,240
sink so low as to have to come here

637
00:26:07,240 --> 00:26:08,150
to paint fakes,

638
00:26:08,680 --> 00:26:10,480
I'd rather go back home and farm.

639
00:26:12,010 --> 00:26:13,740
Here, have some pickles.

640
00:26:14,550 --> 00:26:15,010
Zhuang.

641
00:26:15,140 --> 00:26:17,110
How's your prep
for the troupe audition going?

642
00:26:17,110 --> 00:26:18,040
It's going okay.

643
00:26:19,700 --> 00:26:20,320
By the way,

644
00:26:21,090 --> 00:26:22,940
when you're acting on set,

645
00:26:23,090 --> 00:26:24,890
are there a lot of people around?

646
00:26:25,110 --> 00:26:26,330
Tons.

647
00:26:26,460 --> 00:26:27,520
Do you get nervous?

648
00:26:28,960 --> 00:26:29,470
I do.

649
00:26:32,610 --> 00:26:32,980
Here.

650
00:26:34,330 --> 00:26:34,920
The other day

651
00:26:34,920 --> 00:26:36,130
in class,

652
00:26:36,550 --> 00:26:37,610
the teacher brought some students

653
00:26:37,610 --> 00:26:38,370
to observe.

654
00:26:38,390 --> 00:26:39,810
With so many people, and pros at that,

655
00:26:39,810 --> 00:26:41,010
I got really nervous.

656
00:26:41,200 --> 00:26:42,390
Back when I was

657
00:26:42,550 --> 00:26:43,880
practicing acting,

658
00:26:44,940 --> 00:26:46,380
I wouldn't go anywhere quiet.

659
00:26:46,380 --> 00:26:47,380
I begged people every day

660
00:26:47,380 --> 00:26:48,510
to take me to events,

661
00:26:48,550 --> 00:26:49,530
just to get over

662
00:26:49,530 --> 00:26:50,510
my stage fright.

663
00:26:51,310 --> 00:26:52,400
You have no idea.

664
00:26:52,400 --> 00:26:53,810
Some auditions are packed

665
00:26:53,810 --> 00:26:55,210
with people.

666
00:26:55,460 --> 00:26:56,700
If you don't prepare,

667
00:26:56,720 --> 00:26:58,780
you'll definitely get tongue-tied.

668
00:26:59,050 --> 00:27:00,440
Why don't you give it a try?

669
00:27:00,440 --> 00:27:01,850
Go to some events

670
00:27:02,050 --> 00:27:02,880
and practice.

671
00:27:03,110 --> 00:27:04,140
There's only a month left.

672
00:27:04,140 --> 00:27:06,070
Where can I find a chance like that?

673
00:27:07,110 --> 00:27:07,940
Good point.

674
00:27:09,310 --> 00:27:10,640
You're already eating?

675
00:27:10,770 --> 00:27:12,440
I brought you some extra food.

676
00:27:12,770 --> 00:27:14,140
An actor gifted some seafood
to the director,

677
00:27:14,140 --> 00:27:15,400
so I brought some back.

678
00:27:16,900 --> 00:27:17,560
Thank you.

679
00:27:17,660 --> 00:27:18,320
No problem.

680
00:27:18,610 --> 00:27:19,330
Do you want to join us?

681
00:27:19,330 --> 00:27:20,440
No, no. You guys go ahead.

682
00:27:20,440 --> 00:27:20,930
I'm off.

683
00:27:21,140 --> 00:27:21,550
Mr. Xu!

684
00:27:21,980 --> 00:27:23,380
We're at a loss right now.

685
00:27:23,400 --> 00:27:24,930
Do you think there's a place

686
00:27:24,960 --> 00:27:25,880
for Zhuang Zhuang

687
00:27:25,880 --> 00:27:27,530
to participate in events

688
00:27:27,550 --> 00:27:28,530
for practice?

689
00:27:28,750 --> 00:27:30,110
Perform and practice...

690
00:27:30,110 --> 00:27:31,740
Aren't you taking the troupe audition?

691
00:27:31,740 --> 00:27:33,810
The teacher says I get nervous
in front of a big crowd.

692
00:27:33,810 --> 00:27:34,570
Zhuang,

693
00:27:34,790 --> 00:27:36,530
if only you were like Tao Liangliang,

694
00:27:36,530 --> 00:27:37,140
that would be great.

695
00:27:37,140 --> 00:27:40,670
The more people watching him play sax,
the more excited he gets.

696
00:27:40,750 --> 00:27:42,160
How about an international stage?

697
00:27:42,160 --> 00:27:43,420
International stage?

698
00:27:43,660 --> 00:27:44,720
Republic of China.

699
00:27:48,030 --> 00:27:49,350
Is this the place?

700
00:27:50,290 --> 00:27:51,240
This is it.

701
00:27:51,310 --> 00:27:53,030
Didn't he say next to the main gate

702
00:27:53,030 --> 00:27:54,070
by the parking shed,

703
00:27:54,070 --> 00:27:55,470
across from the ivy?

704
00:27:59,140 --> 00:27:59,780
He's here.

705
00:28:00,680 --> 00:28:02,610
-Xu, over here.
-Screenwriter Xu.

706
00:28:02,700 --> 00:28:03,900
Screenwriter Xu.

707
00:28:04,050 --> 00:28:05,290
I told you

708
00:28:05,290 --> 00:28:06,220
pretend you don't know me.

709
00:28:06,220 --> 00:28:07,550
Okay. We don't know you.

710
00:28:09,750 --> 00:28:11,250
The production has a limited budget,

711
00:28:11,250 --> 00:28:12,310
but they want professional

712
00:28:12,310 --> 00:28:13,130
singers

713
00:28:13,160 --> 00:28:14,060
and musicians.

714
00:28:14,180 --> 00:28:15,290
The executive director suggested

715
00:28:15,290 --> 00:28:15,980
finding someone

716
00:28:15,980 --> 00:28:16,940
to just lip-sync,

717
00:28:16,940 --> 00:28:18,330
but the director refused.

718
00:28:18,330 --> 00:28:19,790
He said people could tell.

719
00:28:21,310 --> 00:28:22,920
Let me remind you again.

720
00:28:23,070 --> 00:28:23,960
When you go in,

721
00:28:24,010 --> 00:28:25,930
don't say you know me.

722
00:28:26,030 --> 00:28:27,070
We don't know each other.

723
00:28:27,070 --> 00:28:28,850
Just say you're here to audition.

724
00:28:28,850 --> 00:28:30,650
The price is negotiable.

725
00:28:31,660 --> 00:28:32,420
The rest

726
00:28:32,530 --> 00:28:33,500
is up to you.

727
00:28:34,030 --> 00:28:35,070
If you get the part,

728
00:28:35,070 --> 00:28:36,930
it's a proper stage for hundreds.

729
00:28:36,980 --> 00:28:38,040
It'll be recorded.

730
00:28:38,200 --> 00:28:39,000
We'll be on TV.

731
00:28:39,790 --> 00:28:41,520
I'm fine with singing,

732
00:28:41,700 --> 00:28:42,660
but I've never acted before

733
00:28:42,660 --> 00:28:44,010
and I get stage fright.

734
00:28:44,090 --> 00:28:45,050
Don't worry. I'm here.

735
00:28:45,050 --> 00:28:46,000
There's not many people.

736
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:47,250
With your professional skills,
you'll be fine.

737
00:28:47,250 --> 00:28:48,240
You just stand there.

738
00:28:48,240 --> 00:28:49,000
No need to act.

739
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:50,460
Just stand there and sing.

740
00:28:50,640 --> 00:28:52,570
This is the audition place, right?

741
00:28:52,790 --> 00:28:53,830
Didn't he say it's here?

742
00:28:53,830 --> 00:28:54,630
It's right...

743
00:28:57,330 --> 00:28:57,880
Manager.

744
00:28:58,110 --> 00:28:59,570
They're here to audition.

745
00:29:00,110 --> 00:29:01,150
This building.

746
00:29:01,310 --> 00:29:02,890
Second floor, turn left.

747
00:29:02,920 --> 00:29:03,720
It's the acting department.

748
00:29:03,720 --> 00:29:05,050
Just go straight there.

749
00:29:05,090 --> 00:29:05,530
Go ahead.

750
00:29:05,530 --> 00:29:07,310
-Thank you, sir.
-You’re welcome.

751
00:29:07,310 --> 00:29:07,840
Go ahead.

752
00:29:08,290 --> 00:29:09,350
Secure the budget.

753
00:29:12,770 --> 00:29:13,700
Hello, Manager.

754
00:29:15,510 --> 00:29:16,040
Manager.

755
00:29:16,050 --> 00:29:16,540
Um...

756
00:29:16,680 --> 00:29:17,500
-Do you have...
-Go work.

757
00:29:17,500 --> 00:29:18,780
Go do your work.

758
00:29:19,040 --> 00:29:19,510
Okay.

759
00:29:19,720 --> 00:29:20,850
Don't waste my time.

760
00:29:26,990 --> 00:29:30,840
[Actor Waiting Area]

761
00:29:31,090 --> 00:29:31,660
Sir.

762
00:29:32,920 --> 00:29:34,950
Does this director shoot fast?

763
00:29:35,110 --> 00:29:36,420
When's lunch?

764
00:29:36,590 --> 00:29:37,740
We haven't even started filming

765
00:29:37,740 --> 00:29:38,510
and you're already thinking about lunch.

766
00:29:38,510 --> 00:29:39,310
Keep waiting.

767
00:29:39,720 --> 00:29:40,250
No, I...

768
00:29:42,180 --> 00:29:43,450
Food is everything.

769
00:29:44,590 --> 00:29:45,730
Won't let us eat?

770
00:29:48,200 --> 00:29:49,160
When is it?

771
00:29:49,460 --> 00:29:50,510
Don't know.

772
00:29:50,850 --> 00:29:51,750
I brought biscuits.

773
00:29:51,750 --> 00:29:52,200
Want some?

774
00:29:52,200 --> 00:29:53,050
No.

775
00:29:54,350 --> 00:29:55,080
Just hold on.

776
00:30:02,290 --> 00:30:03,680
I'm memorizing my lines.

777
00:30:03,680 --> 00:30:04,570
Keep it down.

778
00:30:08,570 --> 00:30:09,900
Making a ruckus again?

779
00:30:09,920 --> 00:30:10,520
Director.

780
00:30:10,920 --> 00:30:11,720
Let me tell you.

781
00:30:11,720 --> 00:30:13,100
You're all new actors.

782
00:30:13,610 --> 00:30:14,660
Getting into Director Weng's production

783
00:30:14,660 --> 00:30:15,650
is not easy.

784
00:30:15,740 --> 00:30:17,340
-Yes, yes.
-Okay, Director.

785
00:30:17,460 --> 00:30:18,660
Thank you, Director.

786
00:30:19,010 --> 00:30:19,830
At least you have some sense.

787
00:30:19,830 --> 00:30:20,220
Boss,

788
00:30:20,270 --> 00:30:21,290
they said they need to adjust

789
00:30:21,290 --> 00:30:22,270
the shooting schedule.

790
00:30:22,270 --> 00:30:22,790
Wait.

791
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:24,070
Didn't we just adjust it?

792
00:30:24,070 --> 00:30:25,200
Why adjust it again?

793
00:30:25,290 --> 00:30:26,170
Well...

794
00:30:26,570 --> 00:30:27,440
Which scene?

795
00:30:27,940 --> 00:30:30,250
The scene with the butler
and the young lady.

796
00:30:30,250 --> 00:30:31,930
Are you two ready?

797
00:30:32,070 --> 00:30:32,520
Ready.

798
00:30:32,550 --> 00:30:33,710
I'm all ready.

799
00:30:33,790 --> 00:30:35,240
I'll put on the costume
and run it for you.

800
00:30:35,240 --> 00:30:35,760
No need.

801
00:30:35,880 --> 00:30:36,950
We'll talk on set.

802
00:30:37,250 --> 00:30:38,270
I need to go find them.

803
00:30:38,270 --> 00:30:40,870
They change things
every day without warning.

804
00:30:41,310 --> 00:30:41,940
Xu.

805
00:30:42,050 --> 00:30:43,050
Screenwriter Xu.

806
00:30:43,830 --> 00:30:45,070
Screenwriter Xu.

807
00:30:45,400 --> 00:30:47,110
Are the musicians ready?

808
00:30:47,140 --> 00:30:47,720
Ready.

809
00:30:47,750 --> 00:30:48,880
Where's the female singer?

810
00:30:48,880 --> 00:30:49,280
The...

811
00:30:49,380 --> 00:30:49,940
I'm here.

812
00:30:53,000 --> 00:30:54,110
Are we singing now?

813
00:30:55,000 --> 00:30:55,830
No, in a bit.

814
00:30:56,900 --> 00:30:57,790
So beautiful.

815
00:30:57,810 --> 00:30:58,540
Really nice.

816
00:30:58,840 --> 00:30:59,640
Looking good.

817
00:31:02,750 --> 00:31:03,510
PA!

818
00:31:03,960 --> 00:31:04,640
Here.

819
00:31:05,070 --> 00:31:06,200
I... I'll get back to work.

820
00:31:06,200 --> 00:31:06,910
Go ahead.

821
00:31:08,850 --> 00:31:09,420
Zhuang,

822
00:31:10,040 --> 00:31:11,500
this outfit looks great.

823
00:31:11,550 --> 00:31:12,110
It's a bit hot.

824
00:31:12,110 --> 00:31:13,770
You really look like a singer.

825
00:31:22,790 --> 00:31:24,200
Thanks.

826
00:31:24,850 --> 00:31:25,270
Wait.

827
00:31:27,050 --> 00:31:28,830
This must be for Zhuang Zhuang.

828
00:31:28,980 --> 00:31:29,490
Here.

829
00:31:29,770 --> 00:31:30,230
Take it.

830
00:31:33,200 --> 00:31:34,030
Drink it.

831
00:31:34,610 --> 00:31:35,480
It's for you.

832
00:31:47,160 --> 00:31:48,740
What should I do? I'm still a bit nervous.

833
00:31:48,740 --> 00:31:49,740
Don't be nervous.

834
00:31:49,790 --> 00:31:50,660
With your talent,

835
00:31:50,660 --> 00:31:51,850
just relax.

836
00:31:53,330 --> 00:31:54,590
Who are we waiting for?

837
00:31:56,180 --> 00:31:57,130
Ranran,

838
00:31:57,240 --> 00:31:58,490
hurry up!

839
00:31:58,810 --> 00:31:59,270
Ranran.

840
00:31:59,290 --> 00:32:00,510
-Don’t worry.
-You're pretty enough.

841
00:32:00,510 --> 00:32:01,900
-We still have time.
-We won’t be late, right?

842
00:32:01,900 --> 00:32:02,830
Filming a movie?

843
00:32:02,880 --> 00:32:04,500
My place is actually quite suitable.

844
00:32:04,500 --> 00:32:05,070
There are many artists

845
00:32:05,070 --> 00:32:06,130
living at my place.

846
00:32:06,140 --> 00:32:07,460
They're just not very famous yet.

847
00:32:07,460 --> 00:32:08,010
Really?

848
00:32:08,090 --> 00:32:08,440
When you come to film,

849
00:32:08,440 --> 00:32:09,720
let them be extras.

850
00:32:09,740 --> 00:32:10,570
Thirty yuan a day

851
00:32:10,570 --> 00:32:11,770
with lunch included.

852
00:32:12,220 --> 00:32:13,170
That much?

853
00:32:13,500 --> 00:32:14,160
I heard extras

854
00:32:14,160 --> 00:32:15,370
only get 20 a day.

855
00:32:16,720 --> 00:32:17,770
Five for you, five for me.

856
00:32:17,770 --> 00:32:18,310
By the time they get it,

857
00:32:18,310 --> 00:32:19,330
it's just 20.

858
00:32:22,200 --> 00:32:23,930
Then regarding the venue fee,

859
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:25,250
we'll follow the rules.

860
00:32:25,250 --> 00:32:26,310
I'll report a higher amount

861
00:32:26,310 --> 00:32:27,510
and you give me the kickback.

862
00:32:27,510 --> 00:32:28,270
I won't let you lose out.

863
00:32:28,270 --> 00:32:29,460
Hurry up.

864
00:32:30,140 --> 00:32:30,770
There are so many people.

865
00:32:30,770 --> 00:32:32,000
Should we split up?

866
00:32:32,030 --> 00:32:32,960
Let's talk when we get there.

867
00:32:32,960 --> 00:32:33,720
Let's go.

868
00:32:33,720 --> 00:32:35,050
-Talk later.
-Let’s go.

869
00:32:36,880 --> 00:32:38,740
These people will be famous soon.

870
00:32:38,920 --> 00:32:39,520
You all,

871
00:32:39,750 --> 00:32:40,510
perfect!

872
00:32:41,110 --> 00:32:42,680
This is the production manager.

873
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:44,480
He's coming here to film a movie.

874
00:32:44,690 --> 00:32:46,450
-This is the artist I told you about.
-He’s a film producer.

875
00:32:46,450 --> 00:32:47,050
Look.

876
00:32:53,350 --> 00:32:54,010
From Henan.

877
00:32:56,180 --> 00:32:57,510
The one who auditioned.

878
00:32:58,750 --> 00:32:59,660
Xu Shengli,

879
00:32:59,830 --> 00:33:01,290
you are really something!

880
00:33:02,300 --> 00:33:02,910
Manager.

881
00:33:07,770 --> 00:33:08,210
Okay.

882
00:33:08,240 --> 00:33:09,100
Buy everything on this list.

883
00:33:09,100 --> 00:33:10,040
Okay, Manager.

884
00:33:16,710 --> 00:33:17,450
Manager.

885
00:33:17,610 --> 00:33:18,140
Manager.

886
00:33:18,450 --> 00:33:19,870
-Well, we…
-Lin.

887
00:33:20,270 --> 00:33:21,400
Manager, what's up?

888
00:33:22,050 --> 00:33:22,640
Take this,

889
00:33:22,640 --> 00:33:24,270
and give it to the director for me.

890
00:33:24,270 --> 00:33:24,770
At noon,

891
00:33:24,830 --> 00:33:26,500
a TV crew is coming for an interview.

892
00:33:26,500 --> 00:33:27,960
Make sure lunch is arranged properly.

893
00:33:27,960 --> 00:33:28,460
Don't worry.

894
00:33:28,460 --> 00:33:29,220
Here. Take these walnuts.

895
00:33:29,220 --> 00:33:30,290
Go scrub them for me.

896
00:33:30,290 --> 00:33:31,920
Scrub them for at least an hour.

897
00:33:31,920 --> 00:33:33,140
Don't break the tips.

898
00:33:33,530 --> 00:33:34,510
Okay, I will.

899
00:33:34,980 --> 00:33:35,650
Manager.

900
00:33:35,940 --> 00:33:37,230
Manager, listen to me.

901
00:33:37,350 --> 00:33:38,660
The director said the budget was limited,

902
00:33:38,660 --> 00:33:39,240
so I...

903
00:33:39,400 --> 00:33:40,920
Xu, Xu, Xu.

904
00:33:41,720 --> 00:33:43,780
I realized you're really something.

905
00:33:44,270 --> 00:33:44,660
Look.

906
00:33:44,720 --> 00:33:45,590
Even I, as the manager,

907
00:33:45,590 --> 00:33:47,420
don't know how to play the system
as well as you.

908
00:33:47,420 --> 00:33:48,090
You brought in

909
00:33:48,090 --> 00:33:49,330
so many of your friends and relatives.

910
00:33:49,330 --> 00:33:50,570
No, let me explain.

911
00:33:50,570 --> 00:33:51,440
No need to explain.

912
00:33:51,440 --> 00:33:52,220
No need to explain.

913
00:33:52,220 --> 00:33:54,020
I've already told the director.

914
00:33:54,380 --> 00:33:55,460
My place

915
00:33:55,570 --> 00:33:56,160
is too humble

916
00:33:56,160 --> 00:33:57,590
for a big star like you.

917
00:33:57,680 --> 00:33:58,140
Just go.

918
00:33:58,250 --> 00:33:58,870
Amen.

919
00:33:58,900 --> 00:33:59,900
Amen.

920
00:33:59,900 --> 00:34:00,610
-Manager.
-Just go.

921
00:34:00,610 --> 00:34:01,510
Amen.

922
00:34:06,490 --> 00:34:09,360
[Seasons Change Hostel]

923
00:34:10,290 --> 00:34:11,030
Mr. Xu.

924
00:34:13,520 --> 00:34:14,920
Did you see the director?

925
00:34:15,350 --> 00:34:15,949
I did.

926
00:34:17,260 --> 00:34:18,790
The director is quite busy.

927
00:34:18,840 --> 00:34:19,820
He said hello to me,

928
00:34:19,820 --> 00:34:21,020
and went back to work.

929
00:34:23,030 --> 00:34:24,130
I don't know much

930
00:34:24,130 --> 00:34:25,230
about your crew.

931
00:34:25,630 --> 00:34:26,699
But technically,

932
00:34:27,010 --> 00:34:27,860
we all got in

933
00:34:27,860 --> 00:34:28,989
through auditions.

934
00:34:29,130 --> 00:34:31,460
The director shouldn't blame you, right?

935
00:34:33,820 --> 00:34:35,699
I just joined the crew too

936
00:34:36,440 --> 00:34:38,770
and I was pulling strings behind his back.

937
00:34:38,960 --> 00:34:40,250
Although I meant well,

938
00:34:41,030 --> 00:34:42,550
I got busted, didn't I?

939
00:34:44,320 --> 00:34:45,900
My manager told me

940
00:34:45,900 --> 00:34:47,560
that he spoke to the director.

941
00:34:48,440 --> 00:34:49,800
He said that from now on,

942
00:34:50,230 --> 00:34:51,690
I don't have to go anymore.

943
00:34:56,340 --> 00:34:57,400
It's that serious?

944
00:34:58,280 --> 00:34:59,500
Then... then let's go together

945
00:34:59,500 --> 00:35:00,570
to explain to the director.

946
00:35:00,570 --> 00:35:01,150
How about that?

947
00:35:01,150 --> 00:35:01,880
No, no.

948
00:35:02,780 --> 00:35:03,940
That would make things worse.

949
00:35:03,940 --> 00:35:05,030
Really, no need.

950
00:35:06,710 --> 00:35:07,660
Right now, I...

951
00:35:07,860 --> 00:35:09,830
I can't really say how I feel.

952
00:35:10,980 --> 00:35:12,410
It feels like I...

953
00:35:13,190 --> 00:35:14,880
like I did something wrong.

954
00:35:15,360 --> 00:35:16,690
Like I let someone down.

955
00:35:17,510 --> 00:35:18,280
But I'm not clear

956
00:35:18,280 --> 00:35:19,400
on exactly why.

957
00:35:22,320 --> 00:35:22,840
It's just that,

958
00:35:22,840 --> 00:35:23,900
if Director Weng

959
00:35:24,050 --> 00:35:25,110
doesn't keep me on,

960
00:35:26,630 --> 00:35:27,510
I really don't know

961
00:35:27,510 --> 00:35:28,440
what I should do.

962
00:35:29,460 --> 00:35:30,840
You did it to help us.

963
00:35:32,500 --> 00:35:33,050
We can't let you

964
00:35:33,050 --> 00:35:34,110
be punished alone.

965
00:35:34,130 --> 00:35:34,590
Then...

966
00:35:35,820 --> 00:35:36,380
How about this?

967
00:35:36,380 --> 00:35:37,380
I'll go tell everyone,

968
00:35:37,380 --> 00:35:38,210
and we can figure something out together.

969
00:35:38,210 --> 00:35:39,170
No, don't.

970
00:35:39,630 --> 00:35:40,980
Don't tell them.

971
00:35:41,710 --> 00:35:43,570
It was supposed to be a good thing,

972
00:35:43,710 --> 00:35:45,280
so let's just protect that goodness.

973
00:35:45,280 --> 00:35:45,890
But...

974
00:35:45,920 --> 00:35:46,650
Besides,

975
00:35:48,860 --> 00:35:50,520
that won't solve the problem.

976
00:35:54,110 --> 00:35:54,970
How about this?

977
00:35:55,210 --> 00:35:55,610
In the next couple of days,

978
00:35:55,610 --> 00:35:57,340
I'll go see the director again.

979
00:35:57,670 --> 00:35:58,590
Like you said,

980
00:35:58,780 --> 00:35:59,980
no matter how it ends,

981
00:36:00,590 --> 00:36:01,210
I have to

982
00:36:01,210 --> 00:36:02,940
explain things clearly to him.

983
00:36:03,690 --> 00:36:04,110
Right.

984
00:36:07,900 --> 00:36:08,500
Thank you.

985
00:36:10,210 --> 00:36:11,210
I feel much better

986
00:36:11,880 --> 00:36:13,080
after letting it out.

987
00:36:14,940 --> 00:36:16,740
I don't feel so stifled anymore.

988
00:36:20,000 --> 00:36:20,670
We should be the ones

989
00:36:20,670 --> 00:36:21,800
apologizing to you.

990
00:36:21,800 --> 00:36:22,400
No need.

991
00:36:24,300 --> 00:36:24,840
Really.

992
00:36:29,260 --> 00:36:29,860
Director,

993
00:36:30,130 --> 00:36:31,760
these are the current issues

994
00:36:31,760 --> 00:36:32,780
in the directing team.

995
00:36:32,780 --> 00:36:34,510
Please see what should be done.

996
00:36:35,590 --> 00:36:36,880
Let's leave it at that for now.

997
00:36:36,880 --> 00:36:38,680
You guys go back to the set first.

998
00:36:38,930 --> 00:36:40,590
-Okay.
-Thank you, director.

999
00:36:53,090 --> 00:36:53,760
Come here.

1000
00:36:59,010 --> 00:37:00,400
Sit down quickly.

1001
00:37:00,400 --> 00:37:02,130
Standing there with your big frame,

1002
00:37:02,130 --> 00:37:03,050
I have to look up

1003
00:37:03,050 --> 00:37:04,300
to talk to you.

1004
00:37:04,840 --> 00:37:05,210
Come.

1005
00:37:12,360 --> 00:37:13,070
Xu.

1006
00:37:14,150 --> 00:37:15,190
When I first asked you

1007
00:37:15,190 --> 00:37:17,070
to join the crew,

1008
00:37:17,400 --> 00:37:18,930
do you remember what I said?

1009
00:37:19,280 --> 00:37:21,050
You said I should come
and watch carefully.

1010
00:37:21,050 --> 00:37:21,450
Right.

1011
00:37:21,730 --> 00:37:22,580
Watch what?

1012
00:37:23,050 --> 00:37:24,750
Watch how everyone works.

1013
00:37:25,630 --> 00:37:26,490
Xu.

1014
00:37:26,730 --> 00:37:28,260
You're a smart kid.

1015
00:37:28,530 --> 00:37:30,190
In this complicated environment,

1016
00:37:30,190 --> 00:37:31,000
you should be able to see

1017
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:32,000
more than others.

1018
00:37:33,090 --> 00:37:35,090
New interpersonal relationships,

1019
00:37:35,570 --> 00:37:36,830
different classes,

1020
00:37:37,300 --> 00:37:38,680
methods of trading,

1021
00:37:39,030 --> 00:37:40,420
clashes between morals...

1022
00:37:40,420 --> 00:37:41,020
Director,

1023
00:37:41,630 --> 00:37:43,260
I overstepped.

1024
00:37:43,630 --> 00:37:44,570
Sit, sit.

1025
00:37:44,780 --> 00:37:45,310
Sit down.

1026
00:37:45,650 --> 00:37:46,000
Sit.

1027
00:37:49,840 --> 00:37:50,480
Ranran

1028
00:37:51,170 --> 00:37:52,080
and Guo Zongbao

1029
00:37:52,530 --> 00:37:53,780
both act well.

1030
00:37:54,510 --> 00:37:55,260
And those two musicians

1031
00:37:55,260 --> 00:37:57,230
you brought in...

1032
00:37:57,340 --> 00:37:58,980
They really saved the day.

1033
00:37:59,440 --> 00:38:01,060
If you were a producer

1034
00:38:01,360 --> 00:38:02,760
or a casting director,

1035
00:38:02,940 --> 00:38:04,940
you would have done a great service.

1036
00:38:05,510 --> 00:38:06,630
But

1037
00:38:06,880 --> 00:38:08,470
this crew is too chaotic

1038
00:38:09,110 --> 00:38:10,230
and you dove headfirst

1039
00:38:10,230 --> 00:38:11,320
into that chaos.

1040
00:38:12,780 --> 00:38:14,280
Do you remember when

1041
00:38:14,420 --> 00:38:16,030
what you said when you came to the studio

1042
00:38:16,030 --> 00:38:16,760
to see me?

1043
00:38:17,360 --> 00:38:19,300
And when you got mad
at the people in the studio,

1044
00:38:19,300 --> 00:38:20,500
what did you say then?

1045
00:38:21,650 --> 00:38:23,310
I said I wanted to do a good job.

1046
00:38:23,320 --> 00:38:24,970
Do a good job at what?

1047
00:38:25,030 --> 00:38:26,030
Writing scripts.

1048
00:38:26,030 --> 00:38:27,290
Being a screenwriter.

1049
00:38:30,530 --> 00:38:32,400
I'll go talk to Manager Xue.

1050
00:38:33,820 --> 00:38:34,730
You'll be paid per day

1051
00:38:34,730 --> 00:38:36,000
for the past few days.

1052
00:38:36,080 --> 00:38:37,970
Your work in the crew

1053
00:38:38,320 --> 00:38:39,040
is now over.

1054
00:38:39,260 --> 00:38:40,300
Director,

1055
00:38:40,420 --> 00:38:41,920
I understand what you said.

1056
00:38:41,920 --> 00:38:42,710
I made a mistake.

1057
00:38:42,710 --> 00:38:43,970
I know I made a mistake.

1058
00:38:44,300 --> 00:38:45,960
Can I still

1059
00:38:45,960 --> 00:38:47,490
work with you in the future?

1060
00:38:49,480 --> 00:38:51,010
I'm a director.

1061
00:38:51,400 --> 00:38:52,670
If you want to learn screenwriting,

1062
00:38:52,670 --> 00:38:54,580
you need to find a screenwriter.

1063
00:39:17,010 --> 00:39:18,210
Well? Did you see him?

1064
00:39:20,280 --> 00:39:21,880
Did you explain everything?

1065
00:39:23,780 --> 00:39:24,640
Say something.

1066
00:39:25,070 --> 00:39:25,630
I saw him.

1067
00:39:28,230 --> 00:39:30,010
He taught me a lesson.

1068
00:39:30,880 --> 00:39:32,290
What do you mean by that?

1069
00:39:34,440 --> 00:39:35,970
Can you still work with him?

1070
00:39:37,880 --> 00:39:40,080
He won't let me work in the crew anymore.

1071
00:39:40,500 --> 00:39:41,960
And he paid me

1072
00:39:42,900 --> 00:39:44,160
my salary from before.

1073
00:39:52,360 --> 00:39:52,920
I'm sorry.

1074
00:39:52,920 --> 00:39:54,120
It's all because of us

1075
00:39:54,400 --> 00:39:55,320
that you lost your job.

1076
00:39:55,320 --> 00:39:56,250
I'm teasing you.

1077
00:39:59,300 --> 00:40:01,080
I'm just kidding.

1078
00:40:01,420 --> 00:40:02,980
Director Weng is great.

1079
00:40:03,670 --> 00:40:04,460
About this,

1080
00:40:04,460 --> 00:40:05,940
he indeed lectured me,

1081
00:40:06,030 --> 00:40:07,300
but he also shared the principle

1082
00:40:07,300 --> 00:40:09,570
about sticking to your dream.

1083
00:40:09,820 --> 00:40:10,840
When I heard that,

1084
00:40:10,960 --> 00:40:13,090
I felt like the Monkey King,

1085
00:40:13,280 --> 00:40:14,460
suddenly enlightened

1086
00:40:14,460 --> 00:40:15,590
by Patriarch Bodhi.

1087
00:40:16,090 --> 00:40:17,550
He let me work on the crew

1088
00:40:17,590 --> 00:40:19,340
because he wanted to observe me.

1089
00:40:19,340 --> 00:40:20,740
He saw my strengths

1090
00:40:20,920 --> 00:40:22,510
but also found some issues.

1091
00:40:22,540 --> 00:40:23,990
In the end, he told me

1092
00:40:24,920 --> 00:40:26,450
I can work in this industry.

1093
00:40:26,610 --> 00:40:27,840
But the most important thing,

1094
00:40:27,840 --> 00:40:29,610
the absolute most important thing,

1095
00:40:29,610 --> 00:40:30,510
is that he's going to introduce me

1096
00:40:30,510 --> 00:40:31,570
to an amazing screenwriter.

1097
00:40:31,570 --> 00:40:32,070
And...

1098
00:40:32,530 --> 00:40:34,090
He'll let me work and learn

1099
00:40:34,090 --> 00:40:35,490
with this screenwriter.

1100
00:40:35,710 --> 00:40:37,260
Just like your Mr. Zheng.

1101
00:40:39,960 --> 00:40:41,290
I was so scared just now!

1102
00:40:44,940 --> 00:40:45,460
Yesterday when you wondered

1103
00:40:45,460 --> 00:40:47,280
if you couldn't work with
Director Weng anymore,

1104
00:40:47,280 --> 00:40:48,300
I immediately thought about how,

1105
00:40:48,300 --> 00:40:49,320
if Mr. Zheng stopped teaching me,

1106
00:40:49,320 --> 00:40:51,520
then all my dreams would be for nothing.

1107
00:41:00,630 --> 00:41:01,320
For people like us

1108
00:41:01,320 --> 00:41:03,050
who came to Beijing on impulse,

1109
00:41:03,110 --> 00:41:03,940
Mr. Zheng and Director Weng

1110
00:41:03,940 --> 00:41:05,210
are like a lifeline.

1111
00:41:06,900 --> 00:41:08,150
If you lost this lifeline

1112
00:41:08,150 --> 00:41:08,860
because of us,

1113
00:41:08,860 --> 00:41:11,190
we'd feel guilty
for the rest of our lives.

1114
00:41:12,400 --> 00:41:13,330
There is no "we."

1115
00:41:13,840 --> 00:41:14,370
Only you.

1116
00:41:15,300 --> 00:41:16,230
You... You're nice.

1117
00:41:16,230 --> 00:41:17,830
I can't say the same for them.

1118
00:41:25,070 --> 00:41:26,280
You're not lying to me?

1119
00:41:26,280 --> 00:41:26,780
No.

1120
00:41:27,360 --> 00:41:28,780
Really, I'm not.

1121
00:41:29,760 --> 00:41:31,730
If you still feel guilty,

1122
00:41:31,730 --> 00:41:33,510
treat me to a soda.

1123
00:41:34,610 --> 00:41:35,570
Why should I treat you?

1124
00:41:35,570 --> 00:41:36,970
Because you feel guilty.

1125
00:41:37,060 --> 00:41:38,120
My treat, my treat.

1126
00:41:38,570 --> 00:41:39,100
My treat.

1127
00:41:42,730 --> 00:41:44,260
How many? Ten bottles?

1128
00:41:45,730 --> 00:41:47,230
Who is the famous screenwriter?

1129
00:41:47,230 --> 00:41:48,590
What has he written? Have I seen any?

1130
00:41:48,590 --> 00:41:50,160
You definitely have!

1131
00:41:50,550 --> 00:41:52,150
He writes all the big hits.

1132
00:41:52,150 --> 00:41:54,280
But... Director Weng won't let me say.

1133
00:41:54,520 --> 00:41:55,880
Stop talking. Stop talking.

1134
00:41:55,880 --> 00:41:57,190
You have to learn your lesson this time.

1135
00:41:57,190 --> 00:41:58,250
Don't mess this up.

1136
00:41:59,710 --> 00:42:01,690
When I no longer cling to love,

1137
00:42:02,110 --> 00:42:04,040
when I'm no longer trapped in hate,

1138
00:42:04,480 --> 00:42:06,660
no longer moved by others' actions

1139
00:42:06,900 --> 00:42:08,440
to joy or sorrow,

1140
00:42:08,980 --> 00:42:11,510
no longer hung up

1141
00:42:11,570 --> 00:42:12,980
on illusory emotions...

1142
00:42:14,010 --> 00:42:15,610
The tears shed upon arrival,

1143
00:42:16,110 --> 00:42:16,960
upon departure...

1144
00:42:16,960 --> 00:42:19,680
Upon departure, will hold no love or hate.

1145
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:21,400
Zhuang.

1146
00:42:22,920 --> 00:42:24,580
When are you joining the crew?

1147
00:42:24,670 --> 00:42:25,820
Just this week.

1148
00:42:26,050 --> 00:42:26,970
That's so fast.

1149
00:42:28,550 --> 00:42:29,840
Will you still rent here?

1150
00:42:29,840 --> 00:42:30,490
Yes.

1151
00:42:31,110 --> 00:42:32,750
This is my root in Beijing.

1152
00:42:33,710 --> 00:42:35,140
No matter where I drift,

1153
00:42:35,170 --> 00:42:36,340
knowing I still have a bed

1154
00:42:36,340 --> 00:42:37,230
in Beijing

1155
00:42:37,230 --> 00:42:38,580
puts my mind at ease.

1156
00:42:43,090 --> 00:42:45,140
If this room suddenly goes quiet,

1157
00:42:45,510 --> 00:42:47,570
it'll take me a while to get used to it.

1158
00:42:48,170 --> 00:42:49,170
That doesn't sound like

1159
00:42:49,170 --> 00:42:50,790
you'll miss me.

1160
00:42:55,340 --> 00:42:56,140
Shen Ranran.

1161
00:42:56,320 --> 00:42:56,980
You got a call.
